-- Gold Fields Reconsiders Platinum Prospect in Finland, Business Day Reports
-- Renee Bonorchis
-- 2010-08-06T05:56:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-06/gold-fields-reconsiders-platinum-prospect-in-finland-business-day-reports.html

          
          
             Gold Fields Ltd.  is re-examining its
platinum prospect in Finland,  Business Day  reported, citing
Chief Executive Officer  Nick Holland .  
 The gold miner is testing a new technology that extracts
platinum group metals from ore bodies and which may make the
project attractive, the Johannesburg-based newspaper said.  
 The Arctic Platinum Project has a resource of 12 million
ounces of platinum and palladium, Business Day said.  
